                        <mrow>\amp= -1.5\abs{1.5}+6</mrow>
                        <mrow>\amp=-1.5(1.5)+6 </mrow>
                        <mrow>\amp= -2.25+6 </mrow>
                        <mrow>\amp=3.75 </mrow>
                    </md>Thus when you are <quantity><mag>6.5</mag><unit base="foot"/></quantity> from the edge, the height in the tent is <quantity><mag>3.75</mag><unit base="foot"/></quantity>.</p></li>
                </ol></p>
            </solution>
        </exercise>


        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>The diagonal length of a rectangle with side lengths <m>L</m> and <m>W</m> is given by:<me>\sqrt{L^2+W^2}</me>Determine the diagonal length of rectangles with:<ol>
                    <li><p>length <quantity><mag>5</mag><unit prefix="centi" base="meter"/></quantity> and width <quantity><mag>12</mag><unit prefix="centi" base="meter"/></quantity></p></li>

                    <li><p>length <quantity><mag>4</mag><unit base="foot"/></quantity> and width <quantity><mag>10</mag><unit base="foot"/></quantity></p></li>
                </ol></p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p><ol>
                    <li><p>When <m>L=5</m> and <m>W=12</m>, we have:<md>
                            <mrow>\sqrt{L^2+W^2} \amp= \sqrt{5^2+12^2}</mrow>
                            <mrow>\amp=\sqrt{25+144}</mrow>
                            <mrow>\amp=\sqrt{169}</mrow>
                            <mrow>\amp=13</mrow>
                        </md>The diagonal length of a rectangle with length <quantity><mag>5</mag><unit prefix="centi" base="meter"/></quantity> and width <quantity><mag>12</mag><unit prefix="centi" base="meter"/></quantity> is <quantity><mag>13</mag><unit prefix="centi" base="meter"/></quantity>.
                    </p></li>

                    <li><p>When <m>L=4</m> and <m>W=10</m>, we have:<md>
                            <mrow>\sqrt{L^2+W^2} \amp= \sqrt{4^2+10^2}</mrow>
                            <mrow>\amp=\sqrt{16+100}</mrow>
                            <mrow>\amp=\sqrt{116}</mrow>
                            <mrow>\amp\approx 10.77</mrow>
                        </md>The diagonal length of a rectangle with length <quantity><mag>4</mag><unit base="foot"/></quantity> and width <quantity><mag>10</mag><unit base="foot"/></quantity> is about <quantity><mag>10.77</mag><unit base="foot"/></quantity>.
                    </p></li>
                </ol></p>
            </solution>
        </exercise>


